abstract: The energy giant has been pressured by shareholders to show how it plans to cope with the risks posed to its holdings by potential limits on greenhouse gas emissions.
snippet: The energy giant has been pressured by shareholders to show how it plans to cope with the risks posed to its holdings by potential limits on greenhouse gas emissions.
lead_paragraph: Energy companies have been under increasing pressure from shareholder activists in recent years to warn investors of the risks that stricter limits on carbon emissions would place on their business.

abstract: The chief of a big-data company says using processes that can’t be quantified often means you aren’t asking the right questions.
snippet: The chief of a big-data company says using processes that can’t be quantified often means you aren’t asking the right questions.
lead_paragraph: This interview with Douglas Merrill, chief executive of ZestFinance, a big-data company that focuses on underwriting, was conducted and condensed by Adam Bryant.

abstract: Anderson Cooper’s CNN show at 8 p.m. beat Bill O’Reilly’s highly rated show on Fox News three nights last week in the coveted audience aged 18 to 54. That was a first for CNN.
snippet: Anderson Cooper’s CNN show at 8 p.m. beat Bill O’Reilly’s highly rated show on Fox News three nights last week in the coveted audience aged 18 to 54. That was a first for CNN.
lead_paragraph: On CNN, the plane rises from misty clouds accompanied by an eerie background score while anchors offer intriguing details — some new, some days old — of the disappearance of Flight 370. The reports, broadcast continually, often are augmented by speculation — sometimes fevered, sometimes tempered — about where the flight might have come to rest. And viewers are eating it up.

abstract: Japanese university researchers say that they still feel under pressure to play down the effects of the nuclear disaster.
snippet: Japanese university researchers say that they still feel under pressure to play down the effects of the nuclear disaster.
lead_paragraph: TOKYO — In the chaotic, fearful weeks after the Fukushima nuclear crisis began, in March 2011, researchers struggled to measure the radioactive fallout unleashed on the public. Michio Aoyama’s initial findings were more startling than most. As a senior scientist at the Japanese government’s Meteorological Research Institute, he said levels of radioactive cesium 137 in the surface water of the Pacific Ocean could be 10,000 times as high as contamination after Chernobyl, the world’s worst nuclear accident.

lead_paragraph: Delphi Automotive, a General Motors spinoff that has become a major independent parts supplier, has a forecast for the future of autonomous driving: partly cloudy, with a drizzle of new technology.

abstract: The 30 or so participants say their objective is to build toward a time when the political landscape may have shifted enough that a bill could pass Congress.
snippet: The 30 or so participants say their objective is to build toward a time when the political landscape may have shifted enough that a bill could pass Congress.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In the summer of 2010, it was Harry Reid, the Senate’s Democratic leader, who squelched his party’s efforts to pass a climate change bill, declaring it could never attract enough votes to pass. In the years since, he has rarely spoken publicly about the issue.

abstract: Mono-skiers competing in the sitting super-G are comparable to bicyclists riding on snow slopes.
snippet: Mono-skiers competing in the sitting super-G are comparable to bicyclists riding on snow slopes.
lead_paragraph: KRASNAYA POLYANA, Russia — Heath Calhoun was disappointed by how he fared in his ski race at the Paralympic Games on Sunday. He was hoping to win a medal. He was expecting to win a medal. He did not. He came in fourth. He was not satisfied, but in one way he was, because he crossed the finish line.
